			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2016</a> paper:</span><br><i>Language Design and Implementation for the Domain of Coding Conventions</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/BoryanaGoncharenko.html">Boryana Goncharenko</a>, <a href="../profile/VadimZaytsev.html">Vadim Zaytsev</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1145/2997364.2997386">10.1145/2997364.2997386</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3c.html"><span class="tagM">T3C: DSLs</span></a><ul><li> It designs a DSL to specify coding conventions as first-class language artifacts.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1b.html"><span class="tagL">T1B: Static Semantics</span></a><ul><li> Coding conventions are enforced through static constraints/semantic checks over programs.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5b.html"><span class="tagL">T5B: Language Description Analysis</span></a><ul><li> It analyzes programs/language instances against a formalized convention description.
</li></ul></li></ul>
